<body>
  <h1>Art Investment Glossary</h1>

  <div class="accordion">
    <div class="accordion-header">Abstract Art</div>
    <div class="accordion-content">
      Art that does not attempt to represent reality, instead using shapes, colours, and forms for expression.
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="accordion">
    <div class="accordion-header">Appraisal</div>
    <div class="accordion-content">
      A professional valuation of an artwork’s fair market value for investment, insurance, or resale purposes.
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="accordion">
    <div class="accordion-header">Auction House</div>
    <div class="accordion-content">
      Institutions like Christie’s, Sotheby’s, or Phillips that sell artworks via public bidding, often influencing global market trends.
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="accordion">
    <div class="accordion-header">Blue-Chip Art</div>
    <div class="accordion-content">
      Works by established, historically significant artists whose markets are considered more stable.
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="accordion">
    <div class="accordion-header">Medium</div>
    <div class="accordion-content">
      The materials used to create an artwork (e.g., oil, acrylic, bronze, photography).
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="accordion">
    <div class="accordion-header">Oil Paint</div>
    <div class="accordion-content">
      Pigments bound with linseed or other oils, prized for richness, durability, and depth of colour.
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="accordion">
    <div class="accordion-header">Provenance</div>
    <div class="accordion-content">
      The documented history of ownership, critical for verifying authenticity and value.
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="accordion">
    <div class="accordion-header">Return on Investment (ROI)</div>
    <div class="accordion-content">
      Financial gain or loss on an artwork relative to its cost.
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="accordion">
    <div class="accordion-header">Securitisation</div>
    <div class="accordion-content">
      Investment model allowing fractional ownership of artworks.
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="accordion">
    <div class="accordion-header">Wall Power</div>
    <div class="accordion-content">
      A term for the visual impact of a work, which influences desirability.
    </div>
  </div>

  <script>
    const headers = document.querySelectorAll('.accordion-header');
    headers.forEach(header => {
      header.addEventListener('click', () => {
        const content = header.nextElementSibling;
        header.classList.toggle('active');
        content.classList.toggle('open');
        if (content.classList.contains('open')) {
          content.style.maxHeight = content.scrollHeight + "px";
        } else {
          content.style.maxHeight = null;
        }
      });
    });
  </script>
</body>
</html>
